review_blob: Pours cloudy amber with a large tan head.Medium lace.Taste has notes of carmel with medium hops presence and bitter.Overall a good ale,it was very 6 $ a pint, too expensive where I get it,too bad ,it is a very drinkable ale.
Pours cloudy amber with a small white head.Very nice nose like aproicot.Sour flavor with a very nice effervesent palate.

This may be the best oatmeal stout I have had yet pours deep black,nice aroma of ripe pears and a superb flavor like dark chocolate and black cherries.I will buy this one again.This was worth every penny.Spread the news Anderson Valley Brewing Co. is making some of the best brews in World.Impressive!
beer_name: Anderson Valley Barney Flats Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Very similar to Fat Tire,but too expensive .I like the double much better than this one.

This is an excellent brew.I like everything about it except the price.It has an incredible palate,leaves your mouth watering and wanting more.Very nice aroma like a ripe apple,tastes like sweet plum with hints of dates.I would buy this for a special occasion.A very rich tasting brew.

This is the perfect dark ale,I have finally found a great ale,with mild hops.It is not too bitter,the sweet malts are perfect.This is the best dark ale I have ever had and I will make my primary daily drinker.I liked everything about it. Perfect! I like this brew better than fat tire.Its the best tasting beer in the world ,I love it.

Pours red brown with beige head.Aroma is of fruit and alcohol.Appearance is cloudy unfiltered.Flavor is of plums.Palate is tangy acidic with an electric aftertaste.Overall a good brew, a little too sour for my tastebuds,maybe an orange peel would help.It has a mild hops presence.
UPDATED: JUL 16, 2007
UPDATED: JUL 16, 2007

This is very good ale,pours amber cloudy.The head small and tan colored,a very average tasting ale with a bite and nose like a grapefruit.This would be a good start if youve never had an ale.Mild hops presence with notes of carmel malts, that are balanced very well together,I could drink 2 pints easy and be very satisfied,I would buy this one again.I would rather have the real european with a stronger ABV #.
Pours amber cloudy,Nose of fruit and alcohol.Taste was sour apple with a medium bitter hops presence.A nice palate and aftertaste.A very drinkable ale.I would buy this brew  again.
This is the most bitter putrid ale ,I have ever had,terrible,I poured it out.All you taste is bitter hops and a ton of it,I hate the flavor.
UPDATED: MAR 23, 2007
UPDATED: MAR 23, 2007

This is a fantastic porter.It pours deep dark brown with a small mocha colored head.It has an incredible flavor of dark chocolate malts with notes of Kola nut ,prunes and mineral water,the water gives it a refreshing electric palate leaving your tongue tingling and mouth watering,it is just exeptional.It has a medium hops presence to let you know youre drinking a porter,but not  an overwhelming bitter,balanced just right,the flavor reminds of a russian imperial stout more than a porter.This is the one of the best Porters/stouts on the planet with a very unique flavor.A must buy.Made by a great California Brewmaster,great job!

Pours black opaque with a large mocha colored head.The Nose is of alcohol and dates.The flavor was of chocolate malts.Mild hops and bitter aftertaste.It had a nice palate leaving you refreshed.Overall a good brew I like Samuel Smiths Imperial Stout and Porter much much better and will stick with them.

This is the perfect Porter,it may very well be the best one on the planet.I envy The British who can get this on tap.The Nose is heavenly with a smell like a ripe pear.It pours dark amber opaque with a lovely mocha colored head.The hops blend is perfect well balanced and full bodied.It has just enough bitter to balance the sweet cholocate malts.I love Porters and this is best Ive ever had,fabulous.The palate is slightly effervescent leaving your mouth watering with a brilliant and electric aftertaste.Bravo Samuel Smith Taddy Porter.A true Brewmaster made this amazing Porter.
UPDATED: MAR 17, 2007
UPDATED: MAR 23, 2007

Pours dark amber a bit cloudy with small tan head,medium hops with the classic bitter taste of a Nut Brown Ale.I enjoyed this one.I like Samuel Smiths Winter Welcome alot better than this  ale.This is one of the only bitters I like,Im not a big fan of them.

This tastes like a Porter to me,it pours black like tar.Nose of hops and chocolate .Too much hops,like most american brews , it overpowers the malts and makes it bitter.This brew was still very good,just not my favorite type of porter.It has a nice palate refreshing.This costs way to much where I buy it.Very small head from the excessive hops,mocha in color.It has notes of coffee and prunes.If they backed off the hops I would buy it again and give it a higher rating.
UPDATED: MAR 11, 2007
UPDATED: MAR 23, 2007
UPDATED: MAR 1, 2007

Better break out your chemistry books,you have to add an orange to break down the sour acids,after adding the orange the beer is great.Cloudy in appearance,pours with a nice thick head and the smell of fruit to the nose.I  highly recommend this great beer.
